***********************
1. Overview
The In-situ Statistical library has been developed to improve runtime of CESM
climate simulations. The intent is to isolate portions of the post-processing
process that can be run in-sutu and provide those portions as functions to be
implemented using the in-situ library. Currently, the functions we have
implemented are as follows:
- min
- max
- mean
- histogram
*- vorticity
*- divergence

The in-situ library takes the 3-dimensional data from CESM and runs the above
statistics on the specified domain.... need more detail once I get more
familiarity with CESM.

